      <h2>Maui's Interior Remodeling Specialist</h2>
      <p>Interior remodeling in Hawaii is different from the mainland. The coastal environment, the humidity, the salt air, the limited material availability, and the unique aesthetic character of Maui homes all shape how renovation projects should be designed and built. Great General LLC has spent five-plus years remodeling interiors on Maui — learning what materials perform, what finishes last, and how to deliver quality work in an island environment.</p>

      <p>Our Hawaii DCCA B License authorizes us to self-perform carpentry, framing, drywall, demolition, and interior finishing work. That means when we quote a bathroom remodel or kitchen renovation, the work is done by our crew under Noel's direct supervision — not handed off to a series of subcontractors at marked-up rates. Your budget goes directly into your project.</p>

      <p>We work on residential homes, vacation rental properties, condominiums, and light commercial spaces across Maui. Whether you're refreshing a rental unit between seasons or doing a full kitchen overhaul in your Kihei home, we bring the same level of attention and accountability to every job.</p>

      <h2>Kitchen Remodels on Maui</h2>
      <p>A kitchen remodel is one of the highest-impact renovation projects you can do — both for daily livability and for property value. Maui kitchens face specific challenges: the open-indoor-outdoor lifestyle demands durable surfaces and finishes that can handle humidity and salt air, while vacation rental kitchens need to balance aesthetics with durability under heavy use.</p>

      <p>Great General LLC handles kitchen remodels from partial refreshes to complete gut-and-rebuild renovations. Our scope includes:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Cabinet removal and installation, including custom carpentry for built-ins and islands</li>
        <li>Interior framing and wall modification for open-concept layouts</li>
        <li>Drywall installation and finish work to prepare for tile and paint</li>
        <li>Flooring installation — tile, luxury vinyl plank, hardwood, and other materials suited to Maui's environment</li>
        <li>Selective demolition of existing kitchen layouts</li>
        <li>Coordination with plumbing and electrical licensed trades for fixture and appliance hookups</li>
        <li>Countertop and backsplash installation prep and finish work</li>
        <li>Maui County permit management for structural modifications</li>
      </ul>

      <p>We advise clients on material selection that balances appearance with performance in Hawaii's climate. Certain wood species, adhesives, and finishes that work beautifully on the mainland degrade quickly in Maui's coastal environment. Five years of experience on the island informs every material recommendation we make.</p>

      <h2>Bathroom Remodeling on Maui</h2>
      <p>Bathroom renovation is one of the most common remodeling projects we handle on Maui, and one where the quality of execution makes an enormous difference. Improperly waterproofed showers, poor tile work, and cheap fixtures are the most frequent sources of water damage in Maui homes — and water damage is particularly costly in Hawaii given material shipping costs and mold remediation requirements.</p>

      <p>Our bathroom remodels are built to last in Hawaii's humid coastal environment. We handle:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Full bathroom gut and rebuild, including demolition of existing tile, fixtures, and drywall</li>
        <li>Selective demolition for partial updates — shower replacement, vanity swaps, flooring only</li>
        <li>Proper waterproofing systems for showers and wet areas — done correctly the first time</li>
        <li>Cement board and tile backing installation</li>
        <li>Tile installation for floors, showers, and feature walls</li>
        <li>Custom shower niches, built-in benches, and carpentry details</li>
        <li>Vanity and mirror installation, including built-in cabinetry</li>
        <li>Coordination with plumbing contractors for fixture work</li>
        <li>Flooring installation throughout the bathroom</li>
      </ul>

      <p>Many of our bathroom projects are in vacation rental units in Kihei, Wailea, and Lahaina — properties where the bathroom needs to look sharp, function reliably, and hold up under high-rotation occupancy. We understand that standard, and we build to it.</p>

      <h2>Interior Framing &amp; Buildouts</h2>
      <p>Changing the layout of a space — opening a wall between rooms, creating a new bedroom, adding a bathroom, framing out a closet system, or reconfiguring an open floor plan — requires structural understanding and precise framing work. Great General LLC has done this kind of work across Maui's diverse building stock, from post-and-pier plantation-era homes to modern concrete-slab construction.</p>

      <p>Interior framing and buildout work includes:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Non-structural and structural wall additions and removals</li>
        <li>New doorway and window opening framing</li>
        <li>Room subdivisions and open-concept conversions</li>
        <li>Closet and storage buildouts</li>
        <li>Ceiling modifications — coffered, dropped, and tray ceiling framing</li>
        <li>Commercial tenant improvement buildouts — office partitions, break rooms, retail fitting</li>
        <li>Maui County permits where structural modifications require inspection</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Drywall Installation &amp; Finishing</h2>
      <p>Drywall work is one of those trades where the difference between good and average is everything. A rushed hang and tape job shows in paint — and shows even more in Maui's strong natural light. Our drywall work is done to a proper finish level for the intended application: Level 4 for standard painted walls, Level 5 for high-sheen paint applications, and textured finishes where appropriate.</p>

      <p>We handle full drywall scopes: demolition of existing drywall, hanging, taping, bedding, sanding, and finish coat — through to primed and ready for paint. This is work we self-perform, which means consistent quality from one crew under direct supervision.</p>

      <h2>Flooring Installation</h2>
      <p>Maui's environment shapes flooring choices. Salt air and humidity make solid hardwood risky in coastal properties. We work with materials that perform in Hawaii: tile, luxury vinyl plank, engineered hardwood, and concrete finishing. We install, repair, and replace flooring in full rooms and throughout whole-home renovations, coordinating seamlessly with the surrounding renovation work.</p>

      <h2>Demolition — Selective and Full</h2>
      <p>Whether you need surgical removal of a single wall or complete strip-out of an entire interior for a full renovation, we handle demolition cleanly and safely. We manage debris removal and disposal, protect adjacent areas and finishes that are staying, and prepare the space for the next phase of work. Selective demolition — removing just the elements that need to change — is a skill of its own, and one we approach carefully.</p>

      <h2>Carpentry &amp; Custom Millwork</h2>
      <p>Built-in shelving, custom cabinetry, window and door trim, baseboards, crown molding, wainscoting, and architectural details — finish carpentry is one of the most visible elements of interior quality. We do custom carpentry and millwork in-house, which gives clients control over design and ensures the work integrates properly with the overall renovation scope.</p>

      <h2>Serving Vacation Rentals, Condos, and Residential Properties</h2>
      <p>Interior remodeling on Maui often involves vacation rental properties — units that need to maximize visual appeal, stand up to frequent guest turnover, and be completed on a tight schedule between booking windows. We've done enough of this work to understand the rental market's constraints and to schedule projects around them where possible.</p>

      <p>We work under HOA rules for condominium projects, coordinate work hours to meet building management requirements, and handle the additional logistics that come with condo renovation work on Maui. We also work on private homes across every community on the island, from Wailea to Haiku.</p>

      <h2>Get a Free On-Site Estimate for Your Remodel</h2>
      <p>If you're planning an interior remodel on Maui — a bathroom renovation, kitchen overhaul, drywall project, flooring replacement, or full interior buildout — call us or submit an estimate request. We come to you anywhere on Maui, walk through the scope, and provide a clear written estimate at no charge.</p>
